SALES BY AUCTION.

ABSTRACT OF SALES BY AUCTION

THIS DAY.

Messrs. GRAHAM and STYLES.—At Malvern-road,

Malvern, at eleven—Household furniture, &c.

Messrs. CAMPBELL and SONS.—At Kirk's Bazaar,

at twelve—Horses, vehicles, &c.

Messrs. BEAUCHAMP BROTHERS.—At Fleming-

ton-road, North Melbourne, at eleven—Household

furniture, buggy, &c.

Messrs. DUNCAN and WELLER. — At Williams-

road, Windsor, at half-past ten—Household fur-

nishings, &c.

Mr. H. D. WESTLEY.—At his rooms, Queen-street,

at two—Suburban and country frehold properties.

Messrs. J. R. BUXTON and Co.—At Mills-street,

Albert-park, at eleven—Household furniture, &c.

Messrs. BAYLEE and Co.—At their rooms, Collins-

street, at eleven—Jewellery, watches, &c.

Messrs. WILLIAM C. YUILLE and Co.—At Vic-

toria Horse Bazaar, at twelve—Racehorses.

Messrs. SMALL and EDWARDS.—At St. Kilda

street, Middle Brighton, at two—Household fur-

niture and effects.

COUNTRY SALES TO-MORROW.

Messrs. CAMPBELL and SONS.—At Sale—Horses.

Messrs. ADAMSON, STRETTLE , and Co.—At Leon-

gatha, Horses.
